s IMX/USDT funding rates every 8 hours using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange applies a base rate of 0.01% plus the premium component, with payments occurring at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. OKX's portfolio margin mode allows cross-collateralization, reducing margin requirements for multi-position funding strategies."}]]}],"$L3",["$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}],"$L8"]}]]}],["$L9","$La"],"$Lb"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
3:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","IMX","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"IMX demonstrates significant funding rate volatility due to its gaming sector positioning and retail trader interest during NFT market cycles. The token's mid-tier volume on OKX creates opportunities for sustained positive or negative funding periods, particularly during gaming announcements or broader market sentiment shifts."}]]}]
4:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"IMX/USDT funding rates on OKX have exhibited clear cyclical patterns, with positive rates averaging 0.03-0.08% during gaming sector rallies and negative rates of -0.02% to -0.05% during broader market downturns. The pair shows pronounced rate spikes during major gaming partnerships or layer-2 scaling announcements. Weekend funding rates tend to be more volatile due to reduced institutional participation, creating enhanced arbitrage windows for retail traders. Gaming token correlations often drive synchronized funding movements across similar assets."}]]}]
5:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Strategy Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Successful IMX funding arbitrage on OKX requires monitoring the 8-hour rate predictions and positioning 2-4 hours before settlement times. The exchange's portfolio margin mode enables efficient capital deployment across multiple gaming tokens simultaneously. Delta-neutral strategies work best when IMX funding rates exceed 0.05% or fall below -0.03%, providing sufficient profit margins after accounting for OKX's 0.02% maker fees. Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities frequently emerge when OKX rates diverge from Binance or Bybit by more than 0.02%."}]]}]
6:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"IMX perpetuals carry elevated liquidation risks due to gaming sector volatility, requiring conservative leverage ratios below 5x for funding strategies. OKX's portfolio margin can amplify losses across correlated gaming positions during sector-wide selloffs. Funding rate reversals often occur rapidly around major gaming industry news, requiring tight stop-losses or hedging via spot IMX positions. The exchange's auto-deleveraging system may force position closures during extreme market stress, particularly affecting larger funding arbitrage positions during low liquidity periods."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does OKX update IMX/USDT funding rates?","answer":"OKX calculates and applies IMX/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The rate is determined using an 8-hour time-weighted average of the perpetual-spot premium, providing more stable rates compared to exchanges with shorter intervals."},{"question":"What makes IMX funding arbitrage profitable on OKX?","answer":"IMX's gaming sector volatility creates frequent funding rate imbalances, while OKX's portfolio margin mode reduces capital requirements for delta-neutral strategies. The exchange's competitive maker fees of 0.02% allow profitable arbitrage when funding rates exceed 0.04% in either direction."},{"question":"Can I use OKX's portfolio margin for IMX funding strategies?","answer":"Yes, OKX's portfolio margin allows cross-collateralization between IMX perpetual and spot positions, significantly improving capital efficiency. This feature enables larger position sizes with the same margin while maintaining delta-neutral exposure for funding collection."},{"question":"What are the main risks when trading IMX funding rates on OKX?","answer":"Primary risks include gaming sector correlation during market stress, rapid funding rate reversals around industry news, and potential auto-deleveraging during extreme volatility. OKX's 8-hour intervals can also create overnight exposure risks that require careful position sizing."}]}]
